description.narrative:
Expected outcomes of the program are threefold: 
1) Women's active participation in local, regional and national decision-making is improved;
2) Citizens (rights' holders including women, men, young people from all social strata) participate in the planning, implementation and monitoring/evaluation of local affairs;
3) Rights holders hold elected officials and local public institutions accountable for the provision of quality services.
To achieve these outcomes mentioned above, the program will support the capacity development of civil society (users committees, local NGOs, youth and women’s groups, Community Based Organizations-CBOs) to implement and promote the principles of good governance. Beyond, it will help establish effective collaborative links between civil society, local elected officials and technical services to ensure their participation in decision-making. As it will be better informed, civil society will be well prepared to negotiate the inclusion of its needs in development processes and exercize control over access to basic social services.
By the end of the intervention, it is expected an improvement of public service provision of water, health and education in the form of faster, higher-quality or better-implemented services.

The first report under this contribution provides information on the results that have been achieved. The following are among other the most important:
The progressive interaction between rights holders and elected authorities at municipality level; this is done through the revitalization of spaces of accountability that were irregular in many municipalities. In some municipalities this was not happened for 10 years
The progressive positive perception of the need to involve women in the management of local affairs; increase their representativeness in decision-making bodies;
The establishment of trust between elected officials and citizens, tending to improve the tax collection rate in certain municipalities;
In addition, there are awareness campaigns organized for young people, which have led them to take civic engagement initiatives in favor of raising the tax collection rate.
